page.title: 20Clubs in Wrentham
page.content:
Women's Institute This club is for ladies. They meet monthly and usually have a speaker. They also arrange flowers in the church. Every year there is a coffee evening at Mrs Liddell senior's house. There is a draw, a cake stall and a bring and buy stall. Mrs Liddell junior makes the coffee.
St. Nicholas' Women's Guild This club is similar to the W.I. but they are connected to the church.
Wrentham Tennis Club The club has 40 adult members and 12 juniors. To join the club costs Â£15 for adults. The team is in the Lowestoft and District League Division 2. Claire Walker
